<b>Posted On:</b> 1:28 p.m. 1/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> You are mistaken<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1224" TARGET=_self>May be no PvP server?</A> (Jourus)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> I just read this post on the EQ message board...anyone got any

<BR>&gt; thights on this? Doesnt look good for Ralos Zek.
<P>Geiger has already said there will be a PvP server in the final (see earlier posts regarding this issue). Additionally, the <a href="http://eq.stratics.com/">EQ Stratics</a> has a poll up about this very issue. The poll has over 2000 votes in with only 50% saying they will not PvP. 37% say they WILL PvP and the other 13% is undecided.
<P>With 37% of the folks planning on playin' the game +PvP, Verant would be FOOLISH to get rid of the +PvP server.
<P><a href="http://personal.lig.bellsouth.net/lig/g/r/grayrage/dbmain.htm">DarkenBane Company</a> is one of many +PvP guilds that will make this server ALOT more fun to play on and elimation of said server would all but make player guilds useless (meaningless in the least). There is inumerable other arguments in favor of the +PvP server seen in many posts below.
<P>-Gray
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
